<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="579" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="8" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,367,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="579">Discussion.</emphasis>
Early literature on aquatic insects of 
<collectingCountry box="[749,816,367,392]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="579">China</collectingCountry>
is rather sparse and widely scattered. Although various groups of aquatic insects have caught the attention of entomologists in 
<collectingCountry box="[1017,1084,404,429]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="579">China</collectingCountry>
and elsewhere, many groups remained unstudied (
<bibRefCitation author="Cheng" box="[389,732,439,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="579" refString="Cheng, L. N., Yang, C. M., Li, D. Q. &amp; Liu, H. M. (2006) Aquatic Heteroptera (Insecta Gerromorpha and Nepomorpha) from Xishuangbanna, Yunnan, China. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 54 (2), 203 - 214." type="journal article" year="2006">
Cheng, Yang, Li &amp; Liu, 
<number box="[671,732,439,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="579" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Until now 
<number box="[875,903,440,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="579" value="12.0">12</number>
species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1034,1163,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Naucoridae</taxonomicName>
are known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1362,1432,439,464]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="579">China</collectingCountry>
, form the checklist, we can know 
<number box="[537,551,476,500]" pageId="8" pageNumber="579" value="9.0">9</number>
species were recorded form Yunnan province, 
<number box="[1096,1110,476,500]" pageId="8" pageNumber="579" value="3.0">3</number>
species were recorded form Hainan province and mostly provinces in 
<collectingCountry box="[641,708,511,536]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="579">China</collectingCountry>
with only one species or no record. It is the first step toward elucidating the fauna of 
<collectingCountry box="[423,492,548,573]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="579">China</collectingCountry>
, we have a lot of work to do in the near future.
</paragraph>
